    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Methionyl Hexapeptide-40 Decapeptide-66 Methionyl Spider Polypeptide-3 Oligopeptide-235) is a single chain fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from Hexapeptide-40, Decapeptide-66, sr-Spider Polypeptide-3 and Oligopeptide-235 with the initiation code for methionine. The fusion peptide contains 1759 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
